 There was a great deal of excitement when Leader of the EFF, Julius Malema entered the Adelaide Tambo Hall in Mhluzi.
Members of the public who have been chosen at random and were given numbers, now await their turn to speak. When a representative of Afriforum said that the amendment will lead to the collapse of the economy, a member of the public announced, “Let it collapse then. It is your economy, not ours.” A journalist from www.mobserver.co.za is currently attending the hearing, and updates on the progress will follow.  PHOTOS and VIDEO: Fire destroys Little Elephant Horrific R555 accident claims lives Grond in die soeklig Hendrina water woes Manne wat met prostese stap is hier Eight injured in taxi collision  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za